questionListItems.title: Can I have 2 credit cards on my app

answer.body: No, you can only use one credit or debit card on the app at a time. To switch to a different card, go to the top left drop-down menu and tap "REMOVE CARD". Then, tap "ADD CARD" and enter your new card information.

questionListItems.title: How do I key in my credit card details?

answer.body:
To add a credit or debit card to your Parking.sg account, simply follow these steps:


1. Open the Parking.sg app and log in with your registered account details or create a new account.
2. Tap the menu icon in the top left-hand corner of the screen and select "Add Card"

3. Enter your cardholder name, card number, expiration date, and CVV/security code.

4. Review the information you entered for accuracy and then submit. If you have already added a card, you can only use one card at a time.



Find the steps to change your card here

questionListItems.title: is the app tag to a mobile number?

answer.body: The Parking.sg app doesn't require a mobile number to be used and is not tagged to one. To pay for parking, simply enter your credit/debit card number, enter the vehicle number, and choose the car park where your vehicle is parked.

questionListItems.title: How do I appeal for a parking fine?
questionListItems.body:
I was activating my parking app while walking away from my vehicle. 
Apparently the parking attendant issued the fine just before I activated my app. I checked the time of issue, it was 1 minute before my parking was activated. Can I write for an appeal please?

answer.body:
If you wish to appeal your ticket, please visit our online appeal channels:

  • For URA car parks: https://www.ura.gov.sg/eAppealWeb/

  • For HDB car parks: https://services2.hdb.gov.sg/webapp/BL16AWESVAPPEAL/faces/JSP/eservices/appeal/BL16RSubmitAppealSearch.jsp

The relevant officers will investigate your case and reply to you directly.

Parking.sg is a mobile app that lets you pay for short-term parking at public car parks using your phone. It replaces paper coupons and is accepted at all coupon-based car parks. Here's how to use it:

  1. Enter your vehicle number in the app

  2. Select the car park where you want to park

  3. Indicate how long you want to park

  4. Pay using your credit or debit card

  5. Start parking

You can also extend your parking session remotely via the app.


Note that if you're parking at a car park with the Electronic Parking System (EPS), you don't need to use the Parking.sg app. Download Parking.sg now to make parking hassle-free!

questionListItems.title: On my debit card statement, I saw multiple  entries titled ‘Parking Pending’ in addition to the ‘Parking Bill’ corresponding to the batched charges. Can you confirm that I have not been double charged? Will the ‘Parking Pending’ disappear?

answer.body:
You have not been double charged. Our app batches up multiple past parking sessions into a single card statement. Parking session payments will be batched into bills every $5 or 2 days (whichever is earlier).


You may refer to the following for more details:

1. You create a parking session with the app. A pending transaction appears on your card statement, on the day of the transaction, following the pattern "Parking.sg PENDING"

2. Each time you create a new parking session, a new pending transaction appears on your card statement

3. After 2 days, or after your pending transactions exceed $5, our billing system consolidates all those pending transactions into a single, new transaction. This is then charged to your card, and appears something like "Parking.sg Bill_abc123"

4. Thereafter, all your individual pending transactions will be cancelled.

5. The 'Bill' tab on your parking history page shows very clearly when each bill is created, and which parking session corresponds to which bill. This should remove any doubt

questionListItems.title: Can I check which vehicle the parking fees were billed to?

answer.body: Yes, you can check your parking fees by going to the bills history page. To get there, tap MENU > HISTORY > BILLS on the top right corner of parking history page.

questionListItems.title: How to print transaction for parking.sg?

answer.body:
To print your parking transaction history from the parking.sg app, follow these steps:

  1. Open the parking history page in the app.

  2. Scroll to the bottom of the page and tap the "export" button.

  3. Select the parking sessions you want to export.

  4. Tap "send" and choose the mode of export.

  5. The easiest way is to select "mail". You will then be able to send an email with the parking history included as a PDF attachment.

That's it! You can now easily print your parking transaction history from the app.

questionListItems.title: How to check what’s my credit card number used for parking SG

answer.body:
To check your credit card details, follow these simple steps:

  1. Tap on the Menu icon (three lines on the top left corner) in the app.

  2. Select "Remove Card". Rest assured, this will not remove your card details yet. Use this page to see the last 4 digit of your card number. If you intend to change card, you may remove and add a different card again.

questionListItems.title: “Free Parking available for selected duration” In this case I no need to pay for parking for my motorcycle?
questionListItems.body: I have parked my motorcycle in Road Side Coupon parking(C0113). This app shows “Free Parking available for selected duration” and I m unable to proceed to next step. In this case I no need to pay right? There is no history also added in this.

answer.body: If you see that parking is free for the duration you need, there's no need to start a parking session. You won't have to pay anything. If you're unsure, you can always check the parking signs in the area or ask a parking attendant.

questionListItems.title: Do I need to purchase a coupon for overnight parking?

answer.body: Yes, the app does support overnight parking scheme. If the amount you pay for parking exceeds the whole-day parking rate, it will be capped at that amount if the car park supports overnight parking. To find out if a car park supports overnight parking, look for the physical signboard located at the car park. It will have more details on the parking scheme.

questionListItems.title: How much hdb carpark with eps charge per day for foreign vehicle ?

answer.body: The EPS system charges for HDB car parks per minute, depending on the location. The rate for non-restricted area car parks is $1.20 per hour, while for restricted area car parks it is $2.40 per hour until 5pm. Check the parking signboards at the car park entrance for more information.

questionListItems.title: Can I start a parking session for multiple vehicles?

answer.body: No, you can only start a parking session for one vehicle at a time using the app.

questionListItems.title: How do I change my vehicle / car plate number?

answer.body:
To update your vehicle information, you can easily delete your existing vehicle and enter the new information.


Here's how:

  1. Open the app and go to the main page.

  2. Find your existing vehicle number field and tap on it.

  3. A list of your saved vehicles will appear. Click on the "X" beside the vehicle you want to delete.

  4. Once the old vehicle number is deleted, tap on the vehicle number field again and enter your new vehicle information. That's it! Your new vehicle information is now updated in the app.

questionListItems.title: Is it safe to store my credit card details in the app?

answer.body: Yes, it's safe to use your credit card in the app. We don't store your payment information on our servers, but instead, we use a secure payment provider to securely save your details. Your information is kept safe even if your phone is lost or stolen. If you would like to remove your credit card information from our secure payment provider, follow the following steps here.
